title: Top things to do this weekend
text:
Top things to do this weekend Feb. 10-11: Motor Trend International Auto Show at Baltimore Convention Center Kenneth K. Lam / Baltimore Sun 
Whether you're looking to test-drive cars or gawk at luxury vehicles more suited for millionaires, the Motor Trend International Auto Show will have more than 500 new cars on display. Each ticket purchase includes a one-year subscription to Motor Trend magazine. 10 a.m.-9 p.m. Friday and Saturday at Baltimore Convention Center, 1 W. Pratt St., downtown. $8-$12 depending on age and date. Kids 12 and younger are admitted free. autoshowbaltimore.com .

Lam / Baltimore Sun) Feb. 10-12: Disney on Ice at Royal Farms Arena Heinz Kluetmeier / Handout 
"Dream Big” is the name of this season’s show, featuring a bunch of classic Disney characters — everyone from Aladdin and Princess Jasmine (“Aladdin”) and Ariel (“The Little Mermaid”) to Anna and Elsa (of “Frozen” fame) — who dream of being something bigger than they are. While on ice skates. Ah, the magic. 10:30 a.m. and 7:30 p.m. Friday; 11 a.m., 2:30 p.m. and 6:30 p.m. Saturday; noon and 4 p.m. Sunday at Royal Farms Arena, 201 W. Baltimore St. $23-$68. royalfarmsarena.com .
